metadata.name: Key of The Nile
metadata.description:
The Ankh is an Egyptian hieroglyph meaning “life,” a symbolic key to the Afterlife. Ancient Egyptian Pharaohs and Kings were entombed holding the Ankh to preserve their immortality. It unlocked their passage from this life to the next, and the Afterlife was equally important to this one.

Myth and Magic drops are blackwork tattoo designs. Those who are dropped the artwork or purchased the piece on secondary have a license to get the artwork tattooed on their body.

You may also use the art as your PFP.
